<h1>DeepSeek Review 2026: Is It the Best Open-Weight AI Model?</h1>
<p><em>Last updated: June 24, 2026</em></p>

<p>When DeepSeek emerged from a Chinese hedge fund in early 2025, the AI world was skeptical. A hedge fund? Building a model that rivals GPT-4? With a training budget under $6 million? It sounded too good to be true. Then the benchmarks landed — DeepSeek topped coding leaderboards, matched Claude on reasoning, and did it all at a fraction of the cost. The industry hasn't been the same since.</p>

<p>Now in 2026, DeepSeek has evolved through multiple major releases. The DeepSeek V4 model represents the culmination of this rapid iteration: a state-of-the-art open-weight model that continues to disrupt pricing norms while pushing performance boundaries. This review covers its capabilities across coding, content creation, data analysis, and research.</p>

<div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-50 to-blue-50 dark:from-cyan-900/10 dark:to-blue-900/10 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
